{"questionId":"14292","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ten students were asked for the distance, in km, from their home to school. Their responses are recorded below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">0.3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;0.4&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3.5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;7&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;8&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;8&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;10</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following box-and-whisker plot represents this data.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/323c0e281eb85ed6f34e777fff91d546b21b3173.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the interquartile range.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;Q<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;− Q<sub>1</sub>&nbsp; 3&nbsp;− 8 ,&nbsp; 3 to 8</p>\n<p>IQR&nbsp;=&nbsp;5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14292","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_1c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the interquartile range.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}